r_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "It seemed clear to me that having an unsized local across a yield point cannot work.\r\nIndeed, you get an ICE with ([playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=46479405f959316eb5d2ea120adcde60)):\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![feature(async_await)]\r\n#![feature(unsized_locals)]\r\n#![feature(gen_future)]\r\n\r\nuse std::future::poll_with_tls_context;\r\nuse std::pin::Pin;\r\nuse std::fmt::Display;\r\n\r\nasync fn foo2() {}\r\n\r\nasync fn foo(x: Box<dyn Display>) {\r\n    let x = *x;\r\n    foo2().await;\r\n    println!(\"hello {}\", &x);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let mut a = foo(Box::new(5));\r\n    let b = unsafe {\r\n        Pin::new_unchecked(&mut a)\r\n    };\r\n    match poll_with_tls_context(b) {\r\n        _ => ()\r\n    };\r\n}\r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/61335/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 1, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/61335/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}